text.paragraph:
                         Renal Impairment:The pharmacokinetics of ganciclovir from a single oral dose of 900 mg valganciclovir tablets were evaluated in 24 otherwise healthy individuals with renal impairment. Decreased renal function results in decreased clearance of ganciclovir and increased terminal half-life

(Table 13

).

Advise patients that valganciclovir may cause temporary or permanent female and male infertility [see

  Warnings and Precautions (

                        5.3

                     ), Use in Specific Populations (

   8.3)

  ].
